  "user_text": "The Hotel Evanstonian process begins when an order is received from a hotel guest by the room service manager.\n\nThe room service manager creates and forwards the order ticket.\n\nNext, several tasks are carried out in parallel:\nIn the kitchen, meals are prepared, while the waiter prepares the cart and non-alcoholic beverages.\nThe sommelier checks if wine is desired.\nIf yes, the sommelier fetches the wine from the cellar.\nThen, it is checked if other alcoholic beverages are desired.\nIf yes, the sommelier prepares these beverages.\n\nAll prepared items are then consolidated, and the waiter delivers the desired order to the hotel guest.\n\nAfter delivery, it is checked if there are no other orders to process.\n\nIf this is the case, the waiter debits the customer's account.\n\nFinally, the customer order is completed.",
  "output_text": "The process begins when an order is received. Once the order is received, an order ticket is created and forwarded to the relevant parties. Following this, meals are prepared according to the order specifications. After the meals are ready, the cart and non-alcoholic beverages are prepared.\n\nNext, there is a decision point to check if wine is desired by the guest. If the guest wants wine, the wine is fetched from the cellar. If the guest does not want wine, the process skips this step. Regardless of the decision, the process continues to the next step.\n\nThe next step involves checking if other alcoholic beverages are desired. If the guest wants other alcoholic beverages, these are prepared accordingly. If not, this step is bypassed. After this decision, the process moves forward.\n\nAll items, including meals, beverages, and any alcoholic drinks, are then consolidated. Once everything is ready, the order is delivered to the guest.\n\nAfter delivering the order, there is a check to see if there are any other orders to process. If there are no other orders, the customer's account is debited for the order. If there are additional orders, the process does not debit the account at this point and instead moves to handle the next order.\n\nFinally, the process concludes, marking the end of the current order handling."
